In this memorandum, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. delegates the authority to the Secretary of State to direct the drawdown of up to $675 million in defense articles, services, military education, and training to provide assistance to Ukraine. This delegation of authority is made under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The Secretary of State is also authorized to make the necessary determinations required under this section to carry out the drawdown. The memorandum concludes by directing the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.